The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     IN THE CITY
                  
	 Kalighat emerged champions beating BNR by nine wickets in the CAB knockout final at the Eden Gardens on Tuesday. Avik Chowdhury bagged five wickets as BNR, batting first, managed 177. Kalighat reached the winning target losing only one wicket, thanks to a brilliant 72-run innings by Saurasish Lahiri.       
	BRIEF SCORES: BNR 177 (Soham Ghosh 51, Avik Chowdhury 5/29, Saurasish Lahiri 2/23). Kalighat 178/1 (Saurasish Lahiri 72 retd ht, M. Ziauddin 59). Kalighat won by 9 wkts.                
	 United Sporting Club signed up Basudeb Mondal while Mohammedan Sporting roped in former Mohun Bagan custodian Imran Khan for the next season on Tuesday. While M. Suresh stayed with East Bengal, United Sports Club are hoping to sign in Mahindra United goalkeeper Subhasish Roy Chowdhury, whose contract with Mahindra expires in 2009.                
	Cricket: CAB league semi-final at Eden from 9.30am.      
	Table tennis: Bata Kalyanjayant meet at Kshudiram Anushilan Kendra from 5pm.                                                                                                                                                                     
